I don't like to be a Yelp snitch but candidly, Not even sure how this place got 3.5 average stars. Ordered eggplant and green curry with chicken. Eggplant wasnt even near cooked and tasted like leather. Curry tasted like salty water (a ton of water) with a few pieces of chicken and the rest was nothing but bamboo shoots and more bamboo shoots. I know people have their off days but this was waaaay off. I do not recommend this place if you like Thai food. Too many other spots to get your fix. I wouldn't give a 1 unless I got sick.

